1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 Nc6 4. Nxc6 dxc6 5. Nc3 (5. d3 Bc5 6. Nc3? { transposes }) 5... Bc5 6. d3? Ng4! { Winning back material and guaranteeing black a better position } 7. Be3 Nxe3 8. fxe3 Bxe3 $17 { with the only dark-squared bishop on the board piercing through white's position (and preventing castling), black has a very comfortable advantage } { [%cal Ge3g1,Ge3c1] } *


